description: This expansive corner loft offers two private bedrooms plus a versatile private den, ideal for a guest room, nursery, or office—a rare find in downtown lofts. It's a fantastic open space with high ceilings, exposed brick, and exposed wood beams. Showcasing ten oversized windows and 12.5-foot high ceilings, this home exudes charm and sophistication. A beautiful kitchen island is perfect for entertaining and casual dining. Modern conveniences include central AC and an in-unit full-size washer/dryer. Residents benefit from the association's elevator, package area, and private storage, all while living moments away from Boston's vibrant Seaport District, featuring attractions like Cisco Beer Garden, F1 Racing, Puttshack, the Institute of Contemporary Art, Trader Joe's, and the Harborwalk. Martin's Park, with its climate-resilient play structures, is conveniently located just outside the building's front door, right next to Fort Point Channel. A fantastic location!
